oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Tintype of Assistant Surgeon William F. Green, USA
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This 1/4 inch plate tintype of Asst. Surgeon William F. Green, 2nd Mich. Cav., USA, was taken in a tent. The buttons in the image were hand guilded, and his cap appears to have the letters MS for "medical service." His service record indicates that he later served with the 1st East Tenn. Cav., USA.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Tennessee State Library and Archives, Nashville, Davidson County, Tennessee
